<Author>maria98
<Content>Very central, good value stay in Madrid. I found Hostal Barrera on this site  decided to try it after reading all the reviews. The approach to the hostal is slightly odd: it's a flat in an appartment building, which has been converted to a hotel. There is 24hours coverage at reception and even though 2 of the 3 staff didn't speak english, they were helpful and very pleasant. The hostal is in a great location, 5-10 minutes walk from the 3 big museums and the Atocha station where the trains to Toledo travel from  2 minutes walk from the nearest underground station. Breakfast is not included but the local cafes were fine. Our room seemed recently decorated and was well appointed and reasonably spacious, and the en suite bathroom was new with a lovely shower. It's good value for money too. The only negative point is that being on the 2nd floor and on a busy road, the room was almost always rather noisy. One can always hear the neighbours above or the blaring cars outside, and even the sound of water being run in other rooms. Honestly, it was worst on day one of our stay  we got used to the noise pretty quickly, but it is a consideration when booking. 
