<Author>Margiemarg
<Content>Very Enjoyable Stay We decided to stay at Hostal Barrera as it was highly recommended to us, and we were not disappointed. It's centrally located (5 to 10 min from the train station and 3 museums). All other major sights in the downtown area are within walking distance. We did not need to take public transportation to get around. Despite being on a busy road, there was minimal noise from the street (windows were very soundproof). It's close to all the major sights and there are a lot of great restaurants in the neighborhood.When we arrived, we were welcomed by a very nice lady who provided valuable information such as restaurants where locals dined and the various sights (e.g. when to visit the museum for free admission). We learned quite a lot about Spain from our brief chats with her everyday. Every part of the room was clean and there was free wi-fi. Overall, Hostal Barrera offers great value. As Madrid was our first stop, our experience was a great start to our Spain trip. Thanks for your hospitality, Nieves! 
